Introduction: Unavailable

Name: Potion
Introduction: Restores a small amount of health.

Name: Mega Potion
Introduction: Restores a moderate amount of health.

Name: Max Potion
Introduction: Fully restores health and maximizes the size of your Health Gauge.

Name: Ancient Potion
Introduction: Fully restores health and maximizes the size of your Health and Stamina Gauges.

Name: Antidote
Introduction: A cure for poison.

Name: Herbal Medicine
Introduction: Removes all traces of poison and restores a slight amount of health.

Name: Nulberry
Introduction: A mysterious berry that cures various blights.

Name: Energy Drink
Introduction: A Guild-approved beverage that boosts your stamina. Helps shake off sleep, too!

Name: Ration
Introduction: Food that restores a bit of stamina.

Name: Rare Steak
Introduction: Provides a moderate boost to your stamina. This one's still red in the middle.

Name: Well-done Steak
Introduction: Provides a moderate boost to your stamina and keeps it at max for a longer period. Meat done right!

Name: Burnt Meat
Introduction: Provides a small boost to your stamina. Can be eaten quickly.

Name: Cool Drink
Introduction: Provides temporary relief from extreme heat.

Name: Nutrients
Introduction: Very slightly increases your maximum health level.

Name: Mega Nutrients
Introduction: Slightly increases your maximum health level.

Name: Immunizer
Introduction: Boosts your natural ability to heal.

Name: Astera Jerky
Introduction: Juicy, dried meat made by Astera's chef. Boosts natural healing and cures bleeding.

Name: Dash Juice
Introduction: Dulls one's sense of exhaustion. Reduces stamina depletion for a time.

Name: Mega Dash Juice
Introduction: Lets you dash without tiring for longer than regular dash juice does.

Name: Might Seed
Introduction: Temporarily strengthens your attacks when ingested by improving energy flow.

Name: Demondrug
Introduction: Boosts your attack power by filling you with—guess what?—demonic strength.

Name: Mega Demondrug
Introduction: Boosts your attack power even more than a regular Demondrug.

Name: Might Pill
Introduction: Temporarily endows you with the strength of a mighty god. Potent!

Name: Adamant Seed
Introduction: Temporarily raises your defense when ingested by hardening tissue.

Name: Armorskin
Introduction: Boosts your defense by turning your skin as hard as rock.

Name: Mega Armorskin
Introduction: Boosts your defense even more than a regular armorskin.

Name: Adamant Pill
Introduction: Temporarily makes your skin as hard as adamant. Potent!

Name: Lifepowder
Introduction: Produces a healing cloud in the area around the user.

Name: Herbal Powder
Introduction: A mysterious powder that produces a cloud around the area that restores health and neutralizes poison.

Name: Demon Powder
Introduction: A mysterious powder that produces a cloud around the area that temporarily strengthens attacks.

Name: Hardshell Powder
Introduction: A mysterious powder that produces a cloud around the area that temporarily strengthens defense.

Name: Honey
Introduction: Highly nutritious honey. Combine this with Potions to craft Mega Potions for maximum potency.

Name: Herb
Introduction: A primary ingredient in potions.

Name: Antidote Herb
Introduction: A primary ingredient in antidotes.

Name: Fire Herb
Introduction: A wondrous, flammable plant. Useful for crafting explosives.

Name: Flowfern
Introduction: This plant's leaves store a great amount of water. A component for making Water Ammo.

Name: Snow Herb
Introduction: A plant that radiates ice-cold air. Use in combinations to create freeze ammo.

Name: Sleep Herb
Introduction: A plant containing sleeping agents. Used to craft tranquilizers.

Name: Ivy
Introduction: A lightweight and extremely strong plant. Used to make nets for pitfall traps.

Name: Smokenut
Introduction: A nut that produces a copious amount of smoke. Combine with other items to create smoke with various properties.

Name: Dragonfell Berry
Introduction: A mysterious berry, rumored for eons to be loathed by dragons. Required to craft Dragon Ammo.

Name: Blue Mushroom
Introduction: A mushroom infused with power-enhancing effects. Used in restorative items.

Name: Mandragora
Introduction: A dangerous fungus said to draw the life out of people. Beware. Required to craft Max Potions.

Name: Nitroshroom
Introduction: A hard-to-find mushroom with the power to generate blazing heat. Required to craft Gunpowder.

Name: Devil's Blight
Introduction: A very rare fungus that pulses with extreme heat. Add to a barrel bomb for a dramatically stronger blast.

Name: Parashroom
Introduction: A mushroom that induces paralysis. Required to craft Tranq Bombs.

Name: Toadstool
Introduction: A poisonous fungus. Can be used as a toxin for knives.

Name: Exciteshroom
Introduction: This one has a very strange aroma. Is it edible? Only one way to find out! Required to craft Farcasters.

Name: Bitterbug
Introduction: A sharp-tasting bug with innate healing abilities. Used as an ingredient in many medicines.

Name: Flashbug
Introduction: An insect that emits a powerful flash when it dies. Required to craft Flash Pods.

Name: Godbug
Introduction: An insect said to live a millennium. Combine it with other items to add their properties to the powder.

Name: Thunderbug
Introduction: An insect that emits electricity when struck. Required to craft Shock Traps and Thunder Ammo.

Name: Baitbug
Introduction: An insect used as fishing bait. A fish favorite, it practically races down the nearest gilly gullet.

Name: Kelbi Horn
Introduction: While not practical when forging equipment, Kelbi horns are a vital component of many items.

Name: Dash Extract
Introduction: A mysterious substance culled from certain monsters that increases endurance.

Name: Nourishing Extract
Introduction: Can be obtained from certain large monsters. Has the ability to amplify the effects of certain medicines.

Name: Screamer Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that emits an earsplitting sonic blast when ruptured. Used to craft screamer pods.

Name: Catalyst
Introduction: Works with other materials to enhance their effects. Cannot be used by itself.

Name: Tranq Bomb
Introduction: A hand grenade used to capture monsters ensnared in traps. Can be slammed against the ground.

Name: Flash Pod
Introduction: Slinger ammo that flashes brightly on impact. Fire it right under a monster's nose to blind it.

Name: Screamer Pod
Introduction: Used as ammo for your slinger. Emits a harsh, high-frequency sound that can disrupt sensitive monsters.

Name: Smoke Bomb
Introduction: Creates a large cloud of smoke wherever it lands.

Name: Poison Smoke Bomb
Introduction: Releases a toxic cloud of mist when used. Also popular as a household bug bomb.

Name: Farcaster
Introduction: Call for a wingdrake to transport you to the nearest camp. Can also be used during battles.

Name: Raw Meat
Introduction: Meat carved from a monster. Can be cooked, combined, or used to set a trap.

Name: Poisoned Meat
Introduction: Raw meat that poisons whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

Name: Tinged Meat
Introduction: Raw meat that paralyzes whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

Name: Drugged Meat
Introduction: Raw meat that puts whatever eats it to sleep. Makes great bait for traps.

Name: Gunpowder
Introduction: A dangerous substance that explodes when struck or heated.

Name: Small Barrel
Introduction: A small, empty barrel.

Name: Barrel Bomb
Introduction: A small time bomb.

Name: Bounce Bomb
Introduction: Launches into the air when set. This modified bomb requires skill to use.

Name: Mega Bounce Bomb
Introduction: An improved version of the bounce bomb. Requires some skill to use.

Name: Large Barrel
Introduction: A large, empty barrel. Combine with gunpowder to make it into a bomb.

Name: Large Barrel Bomb
Introduction: A powerful bomb triggered by external physical impact.

Name: Mega Barrel Bomb
Introduction: An upgraded large barrel bomb. Effective against large monsters.

Name: Spider Web
Introduction: A very sticky web. Used to craft pitfall traps.

Name: Net
Introduction: A sturdy net that supports a certain amount of weight without breaking. Perfect for pitfall traps.

Name: Trap Tool
Introduction: A must-have item for putting together pitfall traps and other kinds of traps.

Name: Pitfall Trap
Introduction: A trap for catching certain large monsters. It is tripped by a heavy weight.

Name: Shock Trap
Introduction: A trap that immobilizes a target. Use it to capture monsters.

Name: Rolled-up Dung
Introduction: A ball of condensed monster dung. Used to make dung pods for your slinger.

Name: Dung
Introduction: Exudes a prodigious smell. Used to make ammo for your slinger called dung pods.

Name: Dung Pod
Introduction: Slinger ammo that releases a strong odor on impact. Causes certain monsters to flee.

Name: Arowana Bait
Introduction: A ball of bait favored by fish of the Arowana family.

Name: Gunpowderfish Bait
Introduction: A ball of bait favored by fish of the Gunpowderfish family.

Name: Goldenfish Bait
Introduction: A ball of bait favored by fish of the Goldenfish family.

Name: Boomerang
Introduction: An unusually-shaped weapon from abroad that returns to its user when thrown.

Name: Binoculars
Introduction: Allows you to see farther and observe from a distance.

Name: Powercharm
Introduction: An amulet that strengthens attacks. Just carrying this gives you demonic strength.

Name: Powertalon
Introduction: A charm that strengthens attacks. Its effects are amplified by the dragon parts it contains.

Name: Armorcharm
Introduction: An amulet that increases defense. Just carrying this hardens your skin like stone.

Name: Armortalon
Introduction: A charm that increases defense. Its effects are amplified by the dragon parts it contains.

Name: Needleberry
Introduction: A nut covered in needle-like spines. Used to make spread ammo.

Name: Blastnut
Introduction: A nut used to make sticky ammo.

Name: Dragonstrike Nut
Introduction: A nut that explodes on impact. Used to make wyvern ammo.

Name: Slashberry
Introduction: Used to make slicing ammo.

Name: Latchberry
Introduction: A nut that bears a spiral groove. Used to make pierce ammo.

Name: Bomberry
Introduction: A nut that ruptures on impact. Used to make cluster bombs.

Name: Flamenut
Introduction: Used to make gunpowder that increases ammo firepower.

Name: Blazenut
Introduction: Used to make gunpowder that greatly increases ammo firepower.

Name: Gunpowder Level 2
Introduction: Combustible powder. Combine with level 1 ammo to raise its level.

Name: Gunpowder Level 3
Introduction: Highly combustible powder. Combine with level 1 ammo to raise its level.

Name: Whetfish Fin
Introduction: A fish fin used to sharpen weapons. Restores sharpness greatly, but good for fewer uses than a whetstone.

Name: Whetfish Fin+
Introduction: A fish fin used to sharpen weapons. Works better than a whetstone, and can be reused if you're lucky.

Name: Sushifish Scale
Introduction: A scale from a Sushifish. Eat to restore a small amount of health. Also works to treat bleeding.

Name: Great Sushifish Scale
Introduction: Scale from a Great Sushifish. Eat to get large health boost, a natural healing boost, and treat bleeding.

Name: Gunpowderfish Scale
Introduction: The scales of a Gunpowderfish. Combine with a large barrel bomb to dramatically increase its firepower.

Name: Great Gunpowderfish Scale
Introduction: The scales of a Great Gunpowderfish. Combine with a large barrel bomb to make a mega barrel bomb.

Name: Burst Arowana Scale
Introduction: The scales of a Burst Arowana. Combine with fire herb to make a large amount of level 2 gunpowder.

Name: Great Burst Arowana Scale
Introduction: The scales of a Great Burst Arowana. Combine with fire herb to make a vast amount of level 2 gunpowder.

Name: Bomb Arowana Scale
Introduction: The scales of a Bomb Arowana. Combine with fire herb to make a large amount of Lv3 gunpowder.

Name: Great Bomb Arowana Scale
Introduction: The scales of a Great Bomb Arowana. Combine with fire herb to make a vast amount of Lv3 gunpowder.

Name: Whetstone
Introduction: A standard-sized whetstone. Use it to restore a weapon's sharpness.

Name: Capture Net
Introduction: A net that can be fired from your slinger. Use it to capture small creatures.

Name: Fishing Rod
Introduction: A tool used for fishing.

Name: BBQ Spit
Introduction: Just what you need to cook meat. A must-have item for any hungry hunter.

Name: Ghillie Mantle
Introduction: Conceal yourself from view temporarily. The effect ends if you perform an attack or take damage.

Name: Temporal Mantle
Introduction: Nullify damage from powerful attacks by automatically evading.

Name: Health Booster
Introduction: Once spiked into the ground, it emits a healing cloud that gradually restores the health of anyone who stands in it.

Name: Rocksteady Mantle
Introduction: Stands firm against certain attacks, and gives you protection against wind pressure, roars, tremors. Also lessens damage.

Name: Challenger Mantle
Introduction: Attracts monsters to you, making it easier to lure them to a favorable position.

Name: Vitality Mantle
Introduction: Nullifies a set amount of damage. The effect ends if more than that amount is taken.

Name: Fireproof Mantle
Introduction: Reduces fire element damage and nullifies fireblight, blastblight, and heat damage.

Name: Waterproof Mantle
Introduction: Reduces water element damage, nullifies waterblight and mud. Lets you wade through deep water easier.

Name: Iceproof Mantle
Introduction: Reduces ice element damage and nullifies iceblight.

Name: Thunderproof Mantle
Introduction: Reduces thunder element damage. Nullifies thunderblight and paralysis.

Name: Dragonproof Mantle
Introduction: Reduces dragon element damage. Nullifies dragonblight while raising dragon element attack.

Name: Cleanser Booster
Introduction: Once spiked into the ground, it emits a healing cloud that cures any abnormal status of anyone who stands in it.

Name: Glider Mantle
Introduction: Extends air time when jumping, lets you ride on strong winds, and makes it easier to mount monsters.

Name: Evasion Mantle
Introduction: Extends the invulnerability window of evasive actions. Dodge attacks at the last minute for an attack boost.

Name: Impact Mantle
Introduction: Adds a stun value to most attacks, and enhances the effect of attacks which cause stun.

Name: Apothecary Mantle
Introduction: Increases the likelihood of weapons with abnormal status attacks to contribute to status buildup.

Name: Immunity Mantle
Introduction: Clears all abnormal statuses and grants immunity from them for a limited amount of time.

Name: Affinity Booster
Introduction: Once spiked into the ground, it emits a cloud of mist that boosts affinity for you and surrounding teammates.

Name: Bandit Mantle
Introduction: Makes attacks against large monsters drop rare and valuable trade-in items.

Name: Normal Ammo 1
Introduction: Ammo for novices. Gets the job done, but it doesn't pack much oomph.

Name: Normal Ammo 2
Introduction: Non-specialized ammo. More powerful than Normal Ammo 1. Capacity: 99

Name: Normal Ammo 3
Introduction: Ammo made with high-quality gunpowder. Each shot packs considerable punch. Capacity: 99

Name: Pierce Ammo 1
Introduction: Armor-piercing ammo that deals multiple hits to some monsters. Capacity: 60

Name: Pierce Ammo 2
Introduction: High-grade armor-piercing ammo. Deals more hits than Pierce Ammo 1. Capacity: 60

Name: Pierce Ammo 3
Introduction: Max-grade armor-piercing ammo. Deals numerous hits. Capacity: 60

Name: Spread Ammo 1
Introduction: Ammo that covers a wide area. Deals multiple hits at close range. Capacity: 80

Name: Spread Ammo 2
Introduction: High-grade ammo that covers a wide area. Deals more hits than Spread Ammo 1. Capacity: 70

Name: Spread Ammo 3
Introduction: Max-grade ammo that covers a wide area and deals numerous hits. Capacity: 60

Name: Sticky Ammo 1
Introduction: Powerful ammo that lodges in a target and explodes. Also stuns. Capacity: 9

Name: Sticky Ammo 2
Introduction: Very powerful ammo that lodges in a target and explodes. Also stuns. Capacity: 9

Name: Sticky Ammo 3
Introduction: Extremely powerful ammo that lodges in a target and explodes. Also stuns. Capacity: 9

Name: Cluster Bomb 1
Introduction: Ammo that fragments into three shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire! Capacity: 3

Name: Cluster Bomb 2
Introduction: Ammo that fragments into four shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire! Capacity: 3

Name: Cluster Bomb 3
Introduction: Ammo that fragments into five shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire! Capacity: 3

Name: Flaming Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that packs a punch against monsters susceptible to fire. Capacity: 60

Name: Water Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that packs a punch against monsters susceptible to water. Capacity: 60

Name: Thunder Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that packs a punch against monsters susceptible to thunder. Capacity: 60

Name: Freeze Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that packs a punch against monsters susceptible to ice. Capacity: 60

Name: Dragon Ammo
Introduction: Elderseal-imbued ammo that packs a punch against monsters weak to dragon. Capacity: 3

Name: Poison Ammo 1
Introduction: Poisons target, but may require several shots. Capacity: 12

Name: Poison Ammo 2
Introduction: Enhanced ammo that inflicts poison. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 12

Name: Paralysis Ammo 1
Introduction: Ammo that causes paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 12

Name: Paralysis Ammo 2
Introduction: Enhanced ammo that causes paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 8

Name: Sleep Ammo 1
Introduction: Ammo that induces sleep. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 12

Name: Sleep Ammo 2
Introduction: Enhanced ammo that induces sleep. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 8

Name: Exhaust Ammo 1
Introduction: Ammo that drains a monster's stamina. Capacity: 12

Name: Exhaust Ammo 2
Introduction: Enhanced ammo that drains a monster's stamina. Capacity: 8

Name: Recover Ammo 1
Introduction: Ammo that restores a small amount of health to an ally upon impact. Capacity: 12

Name: Recover Ammo 2
Introduction: Ammo that restores a moderate amount of health to an ally upon impact. Capacity: 12

Name: Wyvern Ammo
Introduction: Ammo created through years of research into Wyvern's Fire. Capacity: 5

Name: Slicing Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that ejects sharp blades on impact, which can sever tails. Capacity: 30

Name: Tranq Ammo
Introduction: Bowgun ammo used to capture monsters ensnared in traps. Capacity: 8

Name: Demon Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that fills the target with savage amounts of strength. Capacity: 5

Name: Armor Ammo
Introduction: Ammo that makes the target's skin as hard as stone. Capacity: 5

Name: (None)
Introduction: Unavailable

Name: Close-range Coating
Introduction: Arrows designed to deal more damage to nearby targets, at the cost of a reduced maximum range.

Name: Empty Phial
Introduction: A regular old empty phial. Nothing more, nothing less.

Name: Power Coating
Introduction: An arrow coating that increases the attack power of arrows. Capacity: 50

Name: Poison Coating
Introduction: An arrow coating that applies poison effects to arrows. Capacity: 20

Name: Paralysis Coating
Introduction: An arrow coating that applies paralysis effects to arrows. Capacity: 20

Name: Sleep Coating
Introduction: An arrow coating that induces sleep. Capacity: 20

Name: Exhaust Coating
Introduction: An arrow coating that causes arrows to drain monsters' stamina. Capacity: 20

Name: Blast Coating
Introduction: An arrow coating that applies explosive powder to arrows. Capacity: 20

Name: Iron Ore
Introduction: Ore that can be smelted into metal and used for many different purposes.

Name: Machalite Ore
Introduction: Ore that's more difficult to procure than Iron Ore. Produces fine metal.

Name: Dragonite Ore
Introduction: An ore that yields metal superior to that of Machalite. Invaluable for making durable armor.

Name: Carbalite Ore
Introduction: Ore obtained from mining outcrops. Still under research, but known to yield highly pure metal.

Name: Fucium Ore
Introduction: Ore obtained from the Elder's Recess. A mysterious metal, capable of fusing nearly any two materials together.

Name: Earth Crystal
Introduction: Crystallized microbes prized as an abrasive when forging weapons. Mainly found in the Wildspire Waste.

Name: Coral Crystal
Introduction: Crystal prized at the Smithy for use in high-grade abrasives. Mainly found in the Coral Highlands.

Name: Dragonvein Crystal
Introduction: Mined from high rank areas. Many expect this newly-discovered crystal to usher in a new era of metalwork.

Name: Lightcrystal
Introduction: A precious and extremely hard substance with a faint glow. Sometimes used for crafting tools.

Name: Novacrystal
Introduction: High quality Lightcrystal. Highly coveted for its rarity, it's used for only the finest of metalworking.

Name: Firecell Stone
Introduction: A magma-like deposit that only trained hands can work with. Armor made from it is first-class.

Name: Aquacore Ore
Introduction: A valuable mineral used to create charms. Gives off a vibrant glow that mirrors the ocean.

Name: Spiritcore Ore
Introduction: A valuable mineral used to create charms. Gives off a warm, sunny glow.

Name: Dreamcore Ore
Introduction: A valuable mineral used to create charms. Gives off a blazing glow reminiscent of a bonfire.

Name: Dragoncore Ore
Introduction: A valuable mineral used to create charms. Gives off a mysterious glow that grants the holder sagely wisdom.

Name: Armor Sphere
Introduction: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to improve it by a tiny amount.

Name: Armor Sphere+
Introduction: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to improve it by a small amount.

Name: Advanced Armor Sphere
Introduction: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to improve it.

Name: Hard Armor Sphere
Introduction: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to significantly improve it.

Name: Heavy Armor Sphere
Introduction: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to greatly improve it.

Name: Sturdy Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Can be found in bonepiles in the Coral Highlands and Rotten Vale.

Name: Quality Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Its ease of use and hardness allow it to be shaped into better gear.

Name: Ancient Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Can be found in bonepiles in the Ancient Forest. Its size evokes a certain primal quality.

Name: Boulder Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Can be found in bonepiles in the Wildspire Waste. Its size evokes a certain primal quality.

Name: Coral Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Can be found in bonepiles in the Coral Highlands. Its size evokes a certain primal quality.

Name: Warped Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Can be found in bonepiles in the Rotten Vale. Its size evokes a certain primal quality.

Name: Brutal Bone
Introduction: A bone used as crafting material. Can be found in bonepiles in the Elder's Recess. Its size evokes a certain primal quality.

Name: Dragonbone Relic
Introduction: A high quality material found in bone piles. The only remains left of a species of dragon now lost to time.

Name: Unknown Skull
Introduction: A rare material found in bonepiles in the Elder's Recess. It appears to be some kind of animal skull.

Name: Great Hornfly
Introduction: Discovered by Botanical Research. An insect with a giant horn, massive shell, and butterfly-like wings.

Name: Sinister Cloth
Introduction: Suspect cloth the Tailraider Safari dug up from who-knows-where. Drips with an aura of pure evil.

Name: Monster Bone S
Introduction: A material found in bonepiles. Indispensable for both hunting and daily life.

Name: Monster Bone M
Introduction: Bone obtained from large monsters. Strong yet flexible, it's as reliable as steel or wood.

Name: Monster Bone L
Introduction: Bone obtained from large monsters. Hard to work with due to its size, but vital when crafting larger items.

Name: Monster Bone+
Introduction: Bone obtained from large monsters. Hard to obtain, but vital for crafting powerful equipment.

Name: Monster Keenbone
Introduction: Bone obtained from high rank large monsters. It has a razor-sharp tip that retains its strength after forging.

Name: Monster Hardbone
Introduction: Precious bone obtained from high rank large monsters. Their rarity makes them highly sought after.

Name: Elder Dragon Bone
Introduction: A bone from an elder dragon. It exudes the great majesty of the beast that bore it.

Name: Sharp Claw
Introduction: Obtained from small fanged wyverns. Unlike wyvern claws, this is shaped to grip objects.

Name: Piercing Claw
Introduction: Material from high rank small fanged wyverns. Sharp enough that it might serve as a makeshift knife.

Name: Monster Fluid
Introduction: Material obtained from small insects. Mixes with insect gastric fluids to form adhesive.

Name: Monster Broth
Introduction: Material from high rank insects. A rich broth made from only the thickest of monster juices.

Name: Poison Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

Name: Toxin Sac
Introduction: A monster organ filled with an extremely potent toxin. Just touching it is dangerous.

Name: Paralysis Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that contains paralyzing neurotoxins.

Name: Omniplegia Sac
Introduction: A monster organ filled with potent neurotoxins. A single touch can cause paralysis.

Name: Sleep Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that contains a knockout powder capable of inducing sleep.

Name: Coma Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that contains dangerous powder. One whiff can induce a coma.

Name: Flame Sac
Introduction: A monster organ filled with flammable powder. Handle with extreme care.

Name: Inferno Sac
Introduction: A monster organ filled with powder that ignites if it so much as touches air. Danger!

Name: Aqua Sac
Introduction: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve water.

Name: Torrent Sac
Introduction: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve copious amounts of water.

Name: Frost Sac
Introduction: A monster internal organ, filled with extremely low temperature fluid. Handle with care.

Name: Freezer Sac
Introduction: A monster organ with tremendous freezing power. Turns its surroundings to ice.

Name: Electro Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that can store up electricity, which is released on impact.

Name: Thunder Sac
Introduction: A monster organ that can store up large amounts of high voltage electricity.

Name: Bird Wyvern Gem
Introduction: A valuable gem that can be harvested from bird wyverns. Said to fetch a high price on the market.

Name: Shepherd Hare
Introduction: An animal often seen scurrying down narrow side paths. Follow one and you might discover a new shortcut.

Name: Pilot Hare
Introduction: A rare animal that appears on sunny days. They've been said to guide travelers who have lost their way.

Name: Woodland Pteryx
Introduction: A bird common to forested areas. Its bones and feathers resemble those of a prehistoric creature.

Name: Forest Pteryx
Introduction: A rare bird. Though it resembles fossilized species, it also has unprecedented physical features.

Name: Cobalt Flutterfly
Introduction: A beautiful, vibrant butterfly with cobalt-blue wings.

Name: Phantom Flutterfly
Introduction: A brightly-colored, incredibly rare butterfly. The few sightings reported of it have all been on sunny days.

Name: Climbing Joyperch
Introduction: An amphibian that has retained many of its ancient characteristics. Their songs can be heard during rainfall.

Name: Forest Gekko
Introduction: An arboreal lizard often found near brightmoss, predating on the insects that are drawn to the light.

Name: Wildspire Gekko
Introduction: A lizard found near ant hills. Exceptionally large ant hills can draw surprisingly large numbers.

Name: Gloom Gekko
Introduction: A lizard found in caves and other dark places. Their coloration serves as a warning to ward off predators.

Name: Moonlight Gekko
Introduction: A rare lizard whose brightmoss diet causes its tail to glow, a trait it uses to lure in prey.

Name: Vaporonid
Introduction: An Ancient Forest spider that spins webs larger in size than humans.

Name: Scavantula
Introduction: A ground-dwelling spider whose chief diet is rotting flesh. Often found living in groups near bonepiles.

Name: Revolture
Introduction: A carrion-eating bird that scavenges meat from carcasses. It is often spotted flying above large monsters.

Name: Blissbill
Introduction: An herbivorous bird that feeds on fruits and seeds. Comfortable around humans and common near Astera.

Name: Omenfly
Introduction: Insects that emit light from their tails. They usually glow white, but will glow red when in danger.

Name: Augurfly
Introduction: A strange, rare insect that appears during foul weather. They only enter their adult stage during rainfall.

Name: Scalebat
Introduction: A flying wyvern that evolved to adapt to life in caves, taking on a much smaller, bat-like appearance.

Name: Dung Beetle
Introduction: A beetle known to roll balls of monster dung. This process hardens the dung into fine Slinger ammo.

Name: Bomb Beetle
Introduction: A beetle known to roll large stones. Gathering from those stones often yields Slinger bomb pods.

Name: Pink Parexus
Introduction: A fish whose physiology remains almost unchanged from its ancient ancestors. Its spiny fins help ward off predators.

Name: Great Pink Parexus
Introduction: A jumbo-sized Pink Parexus. It must have lived for countless years to reach this size.

Name: Burst Arowana
Introduction: Fish that smell of gunpowder. Use their scales and fire herbs to craft large amounts of gunpowder.

Name: Bomb Arowana
Introduction: Fish that smell of gunpowder. Use their scales and fire herbs to craft large amounts of quality gunpowder.

Name: Great Burst Arowana
Introduction: A jumbo-sized Burst Arowana. Greater in size and volatility. Handle with extreme care.

Name: Great Bomb Arowana
Introduction: A jumbo-sized Bomb Arowana. Greater in size and volatility. Handle with extreme care.

Name: Elegant Coralbird
Introduction: The common name for a female Coralbird. Their vibrant pink color is a result of their coral diet.

Name: Dapper Coralbird
Introduction: The common name for a Coralbird male. Extremely rare, as they only appear for mating.

Name: Andangler
Introduction: A fish bearing a luminous protrusion on its head, which it uses to lure Flying Meduso, its primary prey.

Name: Downy Crake
Introduction: A legendarily rare bird, covered in decadently soft down. It travels atop the back of its symbiotic host.

Name: Bristly Crake
Introduction: A legendarily rare bird, covered in bizarrely stiff, bristly down. It travels atop the back of its symbiotic host.

Name: Hopguppy
Introduction: A fish that bounces across the surface of the water, spreading its pectoral fins to glide farther.

Name: Petricanths
Introduction: Previously known via fossils, this species was thought extinct. Finding otherwise was a real surprise.

Name: Paratoad
Introduction: A toad that releases paralyzing gas on impact. Its effect is potent enough to paralyze even large monsters.

Name: Sleeptoad
Introduction: A toad that releases sleeping gas on impact. Its effect is potent enough to put down even large monsters.

Name: Nitrotoad
Introduction: A toad that secretes an explosive gel on impact. The blast is strong enough to stagger even large monsters.

Name: Wiggler
Introduction: A creature from the Coral Highlands. Match its eye level to put it at ease, allowing you to approach it.

Name: Wiggler Queen
Introduction: A rare creature that appears only on moonlit nights. Watching it dance on the breeze is a truly magical sight.

Name: Vigorwasp
Introduction: An insect that collects restorative nectar in its body, releasing it in a cloud when struck.

Name: Giant Vigorwasp
Introduction: An insect that stores a highly concentrated nectar which leaves a restorative cloud when released.

Name: Flying Meduso
Introduction: A native to the Coral Highlands that moves by riding the wind. Found in areas with the strongest breezes.

Name: Carrier Ant
Introduction: Ants that are known to carry about all sorts of items, including, rarely, large monster materials.

Name: Hercudrome
Introduction: A large beetle with impressive horns. Hercudromes only inhabit seven specific spots in the Ancient Forest.

Name: Gold Hercudrome
Introduction: A glistening golden beetle, thought to bring good fortune. It only appears at night.

Name: Prism Hercudrome
Introduction: A shiny, rainbow-colored beetle. Due to its crepuscular nature, it is only usually seen at dawn and dusk.

Name: Emperor Hopper
Introduction: A grasshopper as big as its moniker would suggest. Its swift, frenetic jumps make it hard to capture.

Name: Tyrant Hopper
Introduction: This previously docile, herbivorous insect underwent phase variation to become a vicious carrion-eater.

Name: Flashfly
Introduction: An insect that emits a bright flash when struck, which is brighter when in a swarm. The flash blinds monsters.

Name: Grandfather Mantagrell
Introduction: A creature that rides air currents to float in midair. Weak to impacts, one good blow will bring it down.

Name: Iron Helmcrab
Introduction: A crustacean found in muddy terrain. It frequently carries hard objects, and occasionally drops piercing pods.

Name: Soldier Helmcrab
Introduction: A crustacean native to the Rotten Vale. They travel in large packs, stripping meat from carcasses.

Name: Emerald Helmcrab
Introduction: A beautiful crustacean usually seen during inclement weather. It's said to be rarer than its gem namesake.

Name: Whetfish
Introduction: A fish with a dorsal fin hard enough to be used to sharpen weapons.

Name: Great Whetfish
Introduction: A jumbo-sized Whetfish. Its dorsal fin surpasses even whetstones in its sharpness.

Name: Gastronome Tuna
